# Classification K-nearest Neighbour Learner

K-nearest neighbor classification. Calls
[`class::knn()`](https://rdrr.io/pkg/class/man/knn.html) from
[class](https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=class).

## Dictionary

This [Learner](https://mlr3.mlr-org.com/reference/Learner.html) can be
instantiated via
[lrn()](https://mlr3.mlr-org.com/reference/mlr_sugar.html):

    lrn("classif.knn")

## Meta Information

- Task type: “classif”

- Predict Types: “response”

- Feature Types: “numeric”

- Required Packages: [mlr3](https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=mlr3),
  [class](https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=class)

## Parameters

|         |         |         |             |                  |
|---------|---------|---------|-------------|------------------|
| Id      | Type    | Default | Levels      | Range            |
| k       | integer | 1       |             | \\\[1, \infty)\\ |
| l       | numeric | 0       |             | \\\[0, \infty)\\ |
| prob    | logical | FALSE   | TRUE, FALSE | \-               |
| use.all | logical | TRUE    | TRUE, FALSE | \-               |

## Examples

``` r
# Define the Learner
learner = lrn("classif.knn")
print(learner)
#> 
#> ── <LearnerClassifKnn> (classif.knn): k-Nearest Neighbour Classifier ───────────
#> • Model: -
#> • Parameters: list()
#> • Packages: mlr3 and class
#> • Predict Types: [response]
#> • Feature Types: numeric
#> • Encapsulation: none (fallback: -)
#> • Properties: multiclass and twoclass
#> • Other settings: use_weights = 'error'

# Define a Task
task = tsk("sonar")

# Create train and test set
ids = partition(task)

# Train the learner on the training ids
learner$train(task, row_ids = ids$train)

print(learner$model)
```
